; A non-ASCII byte (a UTF-8 section sign) inside this comment: §
; Expected: a rendered "Invalid character in stream" diagnostic, exit 1, in
; all 4 modes. Before the F21 fix the display layer swapped out its error
; stream on exhaustion, so the lexer saw a clean end-of-file and everything
; after the bad byte silently vanished (exit 0, empty program) — the
; checkpoint-(d) authoring gotcha where a comment's section sign collapsed a
; whole fixture to empty IR with no diagnostic.
#message m(i32 X).
#local p(i32 X).
p(X) : m(X).
#query qp(free i32 X) : p(X).
